section.para:
This edition of ARR funded research projects which investigated the following aspects:
How climate change will affect flooding and the factors influencing flooding;
How to incorporate climate change into the investigation methodologies used by the engineering profession to estimate design floods;
Updating of the methodology in Australian Rainfall and Runoff so that the outcomes from climate change research (eg. regional dynamic downscaling) can be incorporated easily into the investigation methodology as the science and results become available.
